<paragraph id="8BBC1335B067690842C37CB70171FE62" blockId="20.[166,1225,175,682]" pageId="20" pageNumber="239">
Taxonomic notes. 
<bibRefCitation id="EF926EC4B067690843D97CB7016BFEC2" author="Pisarski, B." box="[449,630,239,266]" pageId="20" pageNumber="239" pagination="375 - 425" refId="ref15414" refString="Pisarski, B. Fourmis (Hymenoptera, Formicidae) d'Afganistan recoltes par Dr. Lindberg // Annales Zoologici. - 1967. - 24, 6. - P. 375 - 425." type="book chapter" year="1967">Pisarski (1967)</bibRefCitation>
described 
<taxonomicName id="4C0368B6B067690841187CA807D5FEC1" authorityName="Pisarski" authorityYear="1967" box="[768,1224,239,265]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Tetramorium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="239" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="striativentre" subSpecies="kabulistanicum">
<emphasis id="B977CF27B067690841187CA800AFFEC1" box="[768,946,240,265]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="239">T. striativentre</emphasis>
subsp. 
<emphasis id="B977CF27B0676908460C7CB707D5FEC1" box="[1044,1224,239,265]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="239">kabulistanicum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
based on the two nest samples from two different localities: 
<specimenCount id="9D05D8BCB067690841617D5700E0FEE1" box="[889,1021,271,297]" pageId="20" pageNumber="239" type="worker">30 workers</specimenCount>
(including 
<typeStatus id="54B8AD97B067690846917D5703C1FE82" pageId="20" pageNumber="239">holotype</typeStatus>
), six gynes and 
<specimenCount id="9D05D8BCB0676908438F7D68011EFE81" box="[407,515,303,330]" pageId="20" pageNumber="239" type="male">one male</specimenCount>
from Cheikhabad (coll. 
<collectorName id="26F676E3B0676908413D7D680078FE81" box="[805,869,303,330]" pageId="20" pageNumber="239">No A</collectorName>
473), and 
<specimenCount id="9D05D8BCB067690841FC7D77079AFE81" box="[996,1159,303,329]" pageId="20" pageNumber="239" type="worker">three workers</specimenCount>
from 
<collectingMunicipality id="6BD8894FB067690842BE7D0803E1FEA2" box="[166,252,336,362]" pageId="20" pageNumber="239">Hassan</collectingMunicipality>
<collectingRegion id="49C7DDD7B0676908431A7D17024EFEA1" box="[258,339,335,361]" country="Iran" name="Gilan" pageId="20" pageNumber="239">Guilan</collectingRegion>
(coll. 
<collectorName id="26F676E3B067690843827D0802C4FEA1" box="[410,473,335,362]" pageId="20" pageNumber="239">No A</collectorName>
314). 
<location id="8EDC45EEB067690840397D170150FEA1" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:03AAA223B061690942BE7D5702C2FF21:8EDC45EEB067690840397D170150FEA1" box="[545,589,335,361]" municipality="Hassan" name="The" pageId="20" pageNumber="239" stateProvince="Gilan">The</location>
specimens from the second locality belong to 
<taxonomicName id="4C0368B6B0676908467F7D0803D3FE41" authority="Radchenko &amp; Scupola, 2015" authorityName="Radchenko &amp; Scupola" authorityYear="2015" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Tetramorium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="239" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pisarskii" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis id="B977CF27B0676908467F7D0803D3FE41" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="239">T. pisarskii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A244725CB067690842CC7D280209FE42" box="[212,276,368,394]" pageId="20" pageNumber="239" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, described above, and are excluded from the type series of 
<taxonomicName id="4C0368B6B067690841D97D280789FE41" authorityName=": Radchenko" authorityYear="1992" box="[961,1172,367,393]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Tetramorium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="239" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kabulistanicum">
<emphasis id="B977CF27B067690841D97D280789FE41" box="[961,1172,367,393]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="239">T. kabulistanicum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(see 
<collectorName id="26F676E3B067690842BE7DD70230FE61" box="[166,301,399,425]" pageId="20" pageNumber="239">Taxonomic</collectorName>
notes to the latter species).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BBC1335B067690842C37DE802A4FD81" blockId="20.[166,1225,175,682]" pageId="20" pageNumber="239">
<taxonomicName id="4C0368B6B067690842C37DE802ACFE01" authorityName=": Radchenko" authorityYear="1992" box="[219,433,431,457]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Tetramorium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="239" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kabulistanicum">
<emphasis id="B977CF27B067690842C37DE802ACFE01" box="[219,433,431,457]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="239">T. kabulistanicum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
well differs from 
<taxonomicName id="4C0368B6B0676908409F7DE8002BFE01" authorityName="Mayr" authorityYear="1877" box="[647,822,432,457]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Tetramorium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="239" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="striativentre">
<emphasis id="B977CF27B0676908409F7DE8002BFE01" box="[647,822,432,457]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="239">T. striativentre</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
first of all by the sculpture of the first gastral tergite: only its basal half is densely longitudinally striato-punctated, the remaining part of tergite is smooth and shiny or at most with fine superficial microreticulation, while in the latter species whole surface of the first gastral tergite is densely longitudinally striato-punctated.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BBC1335B067690842C37E080751FD62" blockId="20.[166,1225,175,682]" pageId="20" pageNumber="239">
By the character of sculpture of the first gastral tergite 
<taxonomicName id="4C0368B6B0676908416D7E080756FDA1" authorityName=": Radchenko" authorityYear="1992" box="[885,1099,591,617]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Tetramorium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="239" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kabulistanicum">
<emphasis id="B977CF27B0676908416D7E080756FDA1" box="[885,1099,591,617]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="239">T. kabulistanicum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
resembles 
<taxonomicName id="4C0368B6B067690842BE7E280234FD41" authorityName="Radchenko &amp; Scupola" authorityYear="2015" box="[166,297,623,649]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Tetramorium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="239" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pisarskii">
<emphasis id="B977CF27B067690842BE7E280234FD41" box="[166,297,623,649]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="239">T. pisarskii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but differs from it by the sculpture of mesosoma and waist, as well as by the sculpture on the head dorsum (see also Taxonomic notes to 
<taxonomicName id="4C0368B6B067690841717EC800F4FD61" authorityName="Radchenko &amp; Scupola" authorityYear="2015" box="[873,1001,655,681]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Tetramorium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="239" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pisarskii">
<emphasis id="B977CF27B067690841717EC800F4FD61" box="[873,1001,655,681]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="239">T. pisarskii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, above).
</paragraph>
